<div><h3>MSPC 3223 - Ethics in the Digital World </h3>  <p><hr>This course connects marketing and communications techniques with their ethical implications. </p>

<p>In this course, we will explore key concepts through current trends and examples, and better </p>

<p>understand our own principles and values through dialogue and the examination of multiple </p>

<p>perspectives. This course flexes our ethical muscles and provides the body of knowledge needed </p>

<p>to act in an ethical manner within the evolving landscape of our digital world. Topics covered </p>

<p>include journalism &amp; media, the &#8220;Copy Left&#8221; v. copyright, and participatory v. voluntary </p>

<p>surveillance. Ethical frameworks used in this exploration include Utilitarianism, Deontology, and </p>

<p>Virtue Ethics.  <br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varied<br><br></p></div>		</td>
	</tr>
</table>
